Welcome to story telling hour.

Once upon a time, there was a little girl. Her name was Princess Makauilani (heavenly eyes)For I knew even before she was born, that she would possess the long lashes that carried in our lineages (true story)😂

However, when Princess Makauilani became a teenager, she rebelled against the Queen! She refused to attend her high school prom! Imagine the dismay the poor Queen endured! 

Henceforth she has made it her mission to make up for her rebellious ways and began to wear make up, and tame that wild hair! 

At long last . . . she is finally wearing the gown I could only once dream of. Mission complete ✨

The end.

The above is the Instagram version.

Reality ⬇️

Excuse me ma’am, you guys aren’t allowed to shoot here without a permit…. Kylee runnnnn!!!!! I have you on high shutter speed 📸

T-Minus 3 days before we’re off! New adventures await us 💫 and we couldn’t be more excited!! 

Also, K+I here are visiting all the way from North Carolina! They decided to go back to our photoshoot location and do an entire hike following our session ♡

Happy New Year!

Better late than never!! I’ve been MIA from socials and posting for a while, with good reason :)

We’ve purchased a home in Tennessee and spent all of Christmas and New Years putting our final touches together ♡ 

I’ve decided to take this time to BE IN the moment, with every. little. detail.

This is the year that I will be intentional with my time!

I’ll be in both places, Hawaii and Tennessee, so don’t hesitate to reach out with an inquiry :)

Meanwhile, I never had the chance to post this beauty and her belly! Mandi-Moon went above and beyond on this day! She is literally the best horse when it comes to photoshoots, she loves the camera and just struts her stuff like she owns the place!  If you’ve ever considered a maternity session with a horse, let me know :)

Do what you love but call it work! 

I worked for the same construction company for about 20 years! But it wasn’t my passion! When Covid hit and the world shut down, it was my time to shine ✨ 

Part 2 of my life began immediately! It was time to utilize the creative side of my brain! I was done with the corporate world! 

I would never have imagined that I’d be here today! Living my dream and calling it work 🙊

Be happy y’all ♡

Portland, Oregon - never disappoints.  This time, we ventured the City! What’s the saying? Keep Portland weird! (more on that later)!

Meet T+K, they live in Oregon and were recently engaged in January!  Happy Engagement to them ♡

I was also more than happy to capture their love as we toured the streets of Portland!  The weather was PERFECT and the streets practically empty.  Portland called us and my couple certainly answered!

Before I get into our crazy hectic rundown on our lives, here’s some beautiful sneak peeks of my couple visiting from Orlando! They recently tied the knot in Columbia and came here to have their love and union celebrated on the shores of Hawaii 🫶🏼

NOW! If you’re interested in learning more about the changes we have going on 👇🏼 keep reading 👇🏼

It was a very hectic week! We’ve been busy buying and selling and once again MOVING!! 

As beautiful as it is in Tennessee, we’ve found it too difficult with the distance and time difference to continue working between Hawaii and the South part of the US! Oh believe me, it’s so disappointing! I love love love that place so much! 

But the beauty of being adventurous is looking forward to change! So the compromise for us, is to relocate ourselves to the 9th island! You guessed it! We’re Las Vegas bound!

People always ask me, don’t you get tired of moving?! Umm, nope! I can’t keep still! I can’t stay in one place too long before I get restless for a change in scenery.

So if you’re planning a trip to the 9th island, don’t hesitate to reach out! I’ll be doing sessions in both locations! 

Be sure to come for a visit 🫶🏼

p.s. more on this beautiful session coming soon 🤩

We just love having Mandy-Moon join our sessions!! It’s always an entire production when she’s a part of the set! It’s reaaaaally hard not to stop and just want to play! Sometimes we have to remind ourselves…. The sun is setting, hurry 😆

H+D together with MM = 🤩✨ MAGIC! They all look so good owning that beach!

Maternity boudoir ✨

Come join us as we capture some baby bump photos at the Shutterhaus Studio!

I often get asked what to wear for their maternity session! You can literally use absolutely anything, or nothing at all.

For this session we opted on an edgy vibe! There’s no rule that you can’t do more than one photoshoot. Do one every month if you want! Capture every stage and every angle of your bump.

Sometimes you achieve better looks with a smaller belly, and for some, it’s best to wait for the belly to be poppin ✨

There’s no right or wrong, just have fun with it 🤗
